<subSubSection id="37E2657C4F28FFFDF0FAFC28FC2F6C1F" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="7F4736F74F28FFFDF0FAFC28FC2F6C1F" blockId="5.[192,1440,931,1083]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F28FFFDF0FAFC28FE326BFF" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[240,423,963,987]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="5 - 6" refId="ref15979" refString="Snelling, R. R. 1993. Collecting on Guana Island, British Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico. Melissa 6: 5 - 6." type="journal article" year="1993">Snelling (1993)</bibRefCitation>
found a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="B8F84D744F28FFFDF2B1FC28FC026BFF" authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[699,919,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D8CEAE54F28FFFDF2B1FC28FC8B6BFF" box="[699,798,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Hylaeus</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
which is not yet described. This constitutes the first native record of the genus for Greater 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F28FFFDF2FFFC0FFC136BDF" box="[757,902,995,1019]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
. In the Greater Antilles the subgenus is now known from 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F28FFFDF154FBE8FE536C3F" box="[350,454,1027,1051]" name="Jamaica" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
(4 species; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F28FFFDF25CFBE8FC906C3F" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[598,773,1027,1051]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref15881" refString="Snelling, R. R. 1982. The taxonomy of some Neotropical Hylaeus and descriptions of new taxa (Hymenoptera: Colletidae). Bulletin Southern California Academy of Sciences 81: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1982">Snelling 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F28FFFDF318FBEFFC056C3F" author="Raw, A." box="[786,912,1027,1051]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="491 - 495" refId="ref15382" refString="Raw, A. 1984. Four new species of bees from Jamaica (Hymenoptera). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 28: 491 - 495." type="journal article" year="1984">Raw 1984</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="07EF76674F28FFFDF3ACFBE8FC7D6C3F" box="[934,1000,1027,1051]" name="Cuba" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(1 species; R. R. Snelling, personal communication, 1995) and Hispaniola (1 species; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B694B064F28FFFDF31AFBC8FC3B6C1F" author="Genaro, J. A." box="[784,942,1059,1083]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="247 - 254" refId="ref13153" refString="Genaro, J. A. 2007. Las abejas (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila) de la Hispaniola, Antillas. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, Espana 40: 247 - 254." type="journal article" year="2007">Genaro 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
